<subpara id="RM000000PFV01QX_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00007LP00000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The ECM determines that there is a malfunction in the ETCS when the throttle valve remains at a fixed angle despite a high drive current from the ECM. The ECM illuminates the MIL and sets a DTC.	</ptxt>
<ptxt>If the malfunction is not repaired successfully, a DTC is set when the accelerator pedal is fully depressed and released quickly (to fully open and close the throttle valve) after the engine is next started.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
